snippet.title: Creedence Clearwater Revival - Have You Ever Seen The Rain (Fan Celebration Version)
snippet.description:
We are celebrating your comments for the official Have You Ever Seen The Rain music video. Thank you for supporting CCR! 

About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.

snippet.title: STRANGER THINGS 5: VOLUME 1 | FINAL TRAILER (2025) | Netflix
snippet.description:
#Netflix #StrangerThings #StrangerThings5

🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
The wait is almost over — the Stranger Things 5 Final Season is here. As Hawkins faces its darkest hour, Eleven and her friends must confront Vecna one last time in a battle that will decide the fate of their world. Starring Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, Sadie Sink, David Harbour, Winona Ryder, and Jamie Campbell Bower, this is the end of an era. Watch the Final Season Trailer 2 for Stranger Things 5, only on Netflix.

The inspiration behind this video:
The wait is over. The Stranger Things 5 Final Season Trailer 2 has arrived, bringing the epic conclusion to Netflix’s most beloved saga. Starring Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, Noah Schnapp, Caleb McLaughlin, and Sadie Sink, this Stranger Things 5 Official Teaser reveals new dangers, new dimensions, and the ultimate showdown between Eleven and Vecna. Join David Harbour as Chief Hopper, Winona Ryder as Joyce Byers, and the full cast including Gaten Matarazzo, Maya Hawke, Joe Keery, Natalia Dyer, Charlie Heaton, and Cara Buono as they face the end of Hawkins’ story. With Jonathan Byers, Will Byers, Nancy Wheeler, Robin Buckley, Steve Harrington, Mike Wheeler, Lucas, Max, and Holly Wheeler, every character’s fate will finally be decided in stranger things season 5 trailer,stranger things.

Experience the power, the mystery, and the heart of Stranger Things Season 5 — only on Netflix. This is where it all ends. Prepare yourself for the darkest chapter yet in the Stranger Things 5 Final Season. Presented by Rotten Tomatoes TV, FilmSpot Trailer, MovieGasm, KinoCheck, EmergencyAwesome, and IGN TV Trailer, this Netflix trailer offer a first look at the spine-chilling events awaiting in STRANGER THINGS 5. • Amazing art, animation, and audio effects
• Lush islands, each with its own musical theme
• Dozens of wacky decorations and structures
• Built-in social features and activities
• New and exciting content is always in the works!

From the fantastical designs provided by Art and Animation, to the iconic sounds and scores from the Audio Team, this musical menagerie is built on the shared work of many. Special thanks to the design, production & programming teams, marketing & promotions, testing & support, and to everyone Big Blue Bubble who make My Singing Monsters possible.
